title: Old diaries, 1881-1901 /
author: Gower, Ronald Sutherland
snippet: The latter kept up a ceaseless slow ofpleasant talk. We have been paying calls on our neighbours, theDrummonds at Swaylands, the Hardinges at South Park,and also to the Sebrights at still incompleted Hever. Penshurst Place is no longer lived in by the De Lisles.

title: Crime
author: Welsh, Irvine
snippet: —  The Simpsons is funny. South Park is neat. I like FamilyGuy.

title: Old diaries, 1881-1901 /
author: Gower, Ronald Sutherland
snippet: Lome camefor a Sunday, and we had Miss Jane Escombe, a neighbour, to meet him — a lady who devotes herself to thebettering the condition of the rural poor. We visitedsome model cottages next day, that she has been theprincipal means of getting built, near the Hardinges atSouth Park, with which Lome (or Argyll, as one had betteraccustom oneself to call him) was much interested. Hammerfield, 11th November.
